@cshannon Yes, I was looking to get it into 6.0.0/5.18.NEXT

The change is minor (all wrapper, no functional). 

Thoughts?

@cshannon yeah, I think the only things left are minor.

1. Any objections to moving activemq-jaas to jul for logging?
2. There is a syntax issue w/ jetty.xml path spec causing authz to go wonky (I'll be able to get into debugger this week)

@lionelraymundi jetty realm is merged into a single JAAS realm in 6.x. This change appears to revert that.

A single JAAS realm simplifies management overall, and we shouldn't need completely separate JAAS realms to do access control across services. 

If you want to separate access for web layer services, simply change the roles in the conf/jetty.xml file and conf/users.properties.
